{emoji:"🌊",name:"Godavari Pushkaram",location:"Rajahmundry and Godavari Banks",desc:"The holiest bathing festival of Andhra Pradesh — held every 12 years when Jupiter enters Leo. The Godavari Pushkaram of 2015 drew 80 million pilgrims to Rajahmundry in 12 days — one of the largest human gatherings on earth. Devotees bathe at specific ghats, perform ancestral rites (pitru tarpan) and visit the string of temples along the river's sacred route through the Eastern Ghats."},
{emoji:"🎊",name:"Ugadi — Telugu New Year",location:"Statewide — March/April",desc:"The most important festival of the Telugu calendar — the new year celebrated with the preparation of Ugadi Pachadi, a dish deliberately combining six tastes (sweet, sour, bitter, salty, hot and astringent) symbolizing life's varied experiences. New clothes, the reading of Panchanga (almanac) predictions, mango leaf toranas at every entrance and temple visits mark a day of profound domestic meaning."},
